<h5>Inform app of it's instance name</h5>
<p><b>Useful to customize specifics for instance</b><br>	
First, set a config variable like this
<pre>heroku config:add APP_NAME=<myappname> --app <myappname></pre>
Then access the variable in rails
<pre>ENV["APP_NAME"] # '<myappname>'</pre>
This is handy if you want to load different config file (say with oauth credentials) based on the app's name or id.


